{
  "text": "The aim of pseudo healthy synthesis is to synthesize a subject-specific 'healthy' image from a pathological one. Generating such images can be valuable both in research and in clinical applications. For example, these images can be used as a means to perform pathology segmentation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , detection [CITATION_3] , to help with the visual understanding of disease classification networks [CITATION_4] and to aid experts with additional diagnostic information [CITATION_5] .",
